haReport:
This mission was flown by:
Kmdr Patrik Schorner
Ltn Otto Kissenberth
Fw Gebhard Schonbaum
Fw Ingemar Beckermann

 The mission was flown from Balatre aerodrome.

Successes include the following: 
On 04/10/1916 near Ercheu.
A Nieuport 11.C1 of Esc 68 was brought down by Patrik Schorner of Jasta 16b.
Jacob Neyrat was made a prisoner of war.
Patrik Schorner was  flying a Albatros D.II.

On 04/10/1916 near Fresnes.
A Nieuport 17.C1 of Esc N.37 was brought down by Detlef Schwarzer of Jasta 16b.
Sergt Etienne Westrelin was killed in action.
Detlef Schwarzer was  flying a Albatros D.II.

On 04/10/1916 near Ecuvilly.
A Nieuport 11.C1 of Esc 68 was brought down by Ingemar Beckermann of Jasta 16b.
Auguste Vallat was not injured.
Ingemar Beckermann was  flying a Halberstadt D.II.

On 04/10/1916 near Ressons.
A Nieuport 17.C1 of Esc N.3 was brought down by Konrad Herxheimer of Jasta 16b.
S/Lt Jean-Luc Lachat was killed in action.
Konrad Herxheimer was  flying a Albatros D.II.
